                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.93/31.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-06-03T11:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1913—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>268. The Chinese Chargé d’Affaires has requested, in the name of his Government,
                    that American consuls in disturbed districts be instructed to extend protection
                    to Chinese citizens when in distress or danger. I await instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Lane Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
